  <h5><b>This application provides real-time information on air quality in different cities around the world.</b></h5>
  <p>
    Specifically, this application allows to :
  <ul class="no-bullet">
    <li>check the Air Quality Index (AQI) of your city or another city in the world.</li>
    <li>see the health implication according to the Air Quality Index.</li>
  </ul>
  </p>
  <h5><b>About the AQI (Air Quality Index)</b></h5>
  <p>
    The AQI (Air Quality Index) is based on air pollutants (PM2.5, PM10, 03, NO2, SO2, CO ) that have adverse effects on human health and the environment.
  </p>
  <p>
    The AQI is divided into six categories. Each category corresponds to a different level of air pollution and health concern.
  </p>
